hitecture#trust-model","content":"Trust model"},"16":{"id":"architecture-14","page_id":"architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/architecture#cold-scans-and-coverage","content":"Cold scans and coverage"},"17":{"id":"architecture-15","page_id":"architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/architecture#coverage-honesty","content":"Coverage honesty"},"18":{"id":"architecture-16","page_id":"architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/architecture#endpoints","content":"Endpoints"},"19":{"id":"architecture-17","page_id":"architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/architecture#configuration","content":"Configuration"},"20":{"id":"architecture-18","page_id":"architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/architecture#where-the-critical-logic-lives","content":"Where the critical logic lives"},"21":{"id":"architecture-19","page_id":"architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/architecture#next-steps","content":"Next steps"},"22":{"id":"architecture-20","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture","content":"\\{/\\* adapted from shade\\@36217c4 docs/03-architecture.md \\*/}"},"23":{"id":"architecture-21","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture","content":"import \\{ Callout } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/callout';"},"24":{"id":"architecture-22","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture","content":"Shade is a monorepo of five TypeScript packages plus one Soroban contract. This page maps each component to its job, then walks the data flow for a full send → scan → claim cycle."},"25":{"id":"architecture-23","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#components","content":"**Reading the diagram:** `crypto` is the dependency-free core everything builds on. The `sdk` wraps all network I/O behind delivery-method adapters. The `cli` is a reference consumer. The `relayer` is a standalone service that never imports `crypto`; it only handles transaction envelopes and credit accounting. The `indexer` is a second standalone service: it watches Horizon's transaction feed and serves the account method's announcement-candidate feed, with no `crypto` (or even `@stellar/stellar-sdk`) dependency, and it never touches the contract. Everything on the `pool` path terminates at the Soroban contract."},"26":{"id":"architecture-24","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#components","content":"Package"},"27":{"id":"architecture-25","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#components","content":"Role"},"28":{"id":"architecture-26","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#components","content":"Key dependency note"},"29":{"id":"architecture-27","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#components","content":"`@shade/crypto`"},"30":{"id":"architecture-28","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#components","content":"DKSAP math: keys, derivation, scanning, recovery, HD/mnemonic, raw-scalar signing"},"31":{"id":"architecture-29","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#components","content":"**Zero** `@stellar/stellar-sdk` dependency. Uses `@noble/curves`, `@noble/hashes`, `@scure/bip39`. Implements StrKey (`G...`) encoding itself, per **SEP-23**."},"32":{"id":"architecture-30","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#components","content":"`stellar-shade`"},"33":{"id":"architecture-31","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#components","content":"`StealthClient`, which hides all Horizon/Soroban I/O behind `send`/`scan`/`claim`. Delivery adapters, typed errors, encrypted sessions, relayer client."},"34":{"id":"architecture-32","page_id":"architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/architecture#componen