th `stdin closed before input was received — pass the value via its flag or environment variable instead`. In non-interactive contexts, supply every needed value via its flag or env var."},"225":{"id":"cli-17","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"Variable"},"226":{"id":"cli-18","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"Used by"},"227":{"id":"cli-19","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"`SHADE_FROM_SECRET`"},"228":{"id":"cli-20","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"`send` (sender secret)"},"229":{"id":"cli-21","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"`SHADE_FEE_PAYER`"},"230":{"id":"cli-22","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"`claim`, `withdraw` (fee-payer secret)"},"231":{"id":"cli-23","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"`SHADE_FUNDING_SECRET`"},"232":{"id":"cli-24","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"`claim`, `withdraw` (funding-account secret — signs the credit-gated relayer challenge)"},"233":{"id":"cli-25","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"`SHADE_KEYSTORE`"},"234":{"id":"cli-26","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"every command (keystore path)"},"235":{"id":"cli-27","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"**Keystore path** resolves as: `--keystore <path>` → `$SHADE_KEYSTORE` → `~/.shade-keys.json`."},"236":{"id":"cli-28","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"**Relayers.** `--relay` (on `claim` and `withdraw`) is **repeatable and comma-separated**: `--relay https://a,https://b` and `--relay https://a --relay https://b&#x60; both work. It falls back to the comma-separated &#x2A;*`SHADE_RELAYERS`** env var when omitted. With more than one URL the client health-probes all candidates in parallel, routes to a healthy one (random by default, spreading users across the set), and fails over on relayer faults. `--verbose` prints the chosen relayer. When none is usable, the error lists every candidate with its rejection reason. See Relayer → Choosing a relayer."},"237":{"id":"cli-29","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"**Indexer.** `--indexer <url>` (on `scan` and `balance`) points account-method discovery at an announcement indexe&#x72; and falls back to the &#x2A;*`SHADE_INDEXER`** env var when omitted (flag wins; a single URL, no list). Horizon remains the source of truth: the scan verifies the indexer's health first, always finishes with a Horizon tail, and degrades silently to the plain Horizon walk on any indexer fault. `scan --verbose` reports the indexer in use."},"238":{"id":"cli-30","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#conventions","content":"**Networks:** `--network testnet` is the default and the **only** accepted value today. Anything else, notably the removed `local` and the not-yet-audited `mainnet`, is rejected with an error. Mainnet (\"public\") arrives after the external audit."},"239":{"id":"cli-31","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"Generate or recover stealth keys and write a keystore. Prints your meta-address."},"240":{"id":"cli-32","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"Flag"},"241":{"id":"cli-33","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"Description"},"242":{"id":"cli-34","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"`--keystore <path>`"},"243":{"id":"cli-35","page_id":"cli","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/cli#shade-keygen","content":"Keystore file path (defaults to 