rnal SAC `transfer` call, so a malicious token contract cannot re-enter and replay the withdrawal."],[1064,"`WrongPasswordError`"],[616,"`WrongPasswordError` / \"Keystore is encrypted but no password provided\""],[642,"> A delivery method is required. Pass `opts.method: 'pool' | 'account' | 'auto'`."],[569,"> native asset **AND** amount > 1 **AND** `'account'&#x60; enabled → &#x2A;*`account`*&#x2A;; otherwise → &#x2A;*`pool`**."],[435,"> Only the `pool` method uses view tags. The `account` method matches on the derived destination address directly, which *is* the full verification."],[827,"≤ now + 600s (`MAX_RELAY_TIMEBOUNDS_SECONDS`); already-expired bounds are rejected up front (`invalid_timebounds`) rather than burning a submit"],[508,"⏳ Reserved slot (*not built*)"],[506,"✅ Implemented"],[507,"✅ Implemented"],[833,"0.1 XLM (`MAX_RELAY_FEE_XLM`)"],[531,"1 XLM reserve (native, reclaimed on sweep) or 1.5001 XLM fronted (token, 0.5 returns to sender)"],[831,"10,000 stroops (`MAX_BASE_FEE`)"],[825,"5 (`MAX_RELAY_OPS`); zero-op inner txs are rejected (`invalid_tx`)"],[1031,"A **credit-gated sponsored claim** signs its proof-of-control over the exact total the relayer debits: the prepared tx's fee **plus** the sponsored-reserve estimate. The SDK prefers the estimate the relayer advertises in `/health` and falls back to its own mirrored 1 XLM constant when `sponsoredReserveEstimateStroops()` returns `undefined`, so a relayer-side change to the estimate no longer breaks gated claims, and a `/health` fault never breaks the claim itself."],[766,"A **relayer** for fee-bumping and reserve-fronting. See Relayer."],[427,"A **stealth address** is the one-time destination a sender derives from your meta-address. It's a normal Stellar `G...` address, but nobody can link it back to your meta-address without your view key."],[991,"A `relayer` **list** enables BYO-relayer discovery: relayed submissions health-probe every candidate in parallel, route to a healthy one, and fail over on relayer faults (see `RelayerPool`). A single string behaves as it always has, with no probing and no new traffic. `relayerSelection` defaults to `'random'`, spreading users across the relayer set instead of herding onto the first entry."],[665,"A CLI prompt (keystore password, secret) hit end-of-file before any input arrived, typical with piped stdin or in CI. The command exits **1** with this message instead of node's old behaviour of silently exiting **0** mid-command as if it had succeeded. In non-interactive contexts, pass the value via its flag or environment variable (e.g. `--password`, `$SHADE_FEE_PAYER`)."],[135,"A coverage claim is only useful if the indexer **owns its failures**. The ingester runs a periodic **feed continuity check** against Horizon's retention bounds, and because a recorded gap is *permanent*, the check fails **closed** in every direction: ingestion never starts before the process's first successful check (a cold start against a broken root document must not silently cross a retention hole); bounds from a root document reporting a different network passphrase are discarded (a mistyped `HORIZON_URL` cannot poison the gap store); and a hole (starting at the cursor ledger itself, whose tail may be partially unserved) is recorded only after **two consecutive observations**, with paging paused in between."],[389,"A fee payer is **required**. If the recipient's pool entry has archived, the CLI transparently submits a `RestoreFootprintOp` first and rebuilds the withdraw on a fresh sequence."],[996,"A method is **required** on every call. Throws `MethodRequiredError` if `opts.method` is missing, `MethodNotEnabledError` if the resolved method isn't in `config.methods`."],[511,"A one-time real Stellar **account** / claimable balance"],[650,"A partial account claim asked for more than the account can pay out while keeping &#x2A;*2× the base reserve (1.0 XLM)** and covering the fee. The error carries `.max`. Retry within it, or do a full sweep (`merge: true` / drop `--no-merge`)."],[658,"A pool withdraw needs an account to pay the Soroban fee, and none was supplied. Pass `feePayer` (CLI: `--fee-payer`, or better `$SHADE_FEE_PAYER`), or route through a relayer with `--relay`."],[768,"A reference **CLI** (`shade`) and a **TypeScript SDK**."],[1089,"A relayer endpoint responded non-2xx; carries `.status` and the relayer's own `.relayerCode` (e.g. `insufficient_credit`)"],[1157,"A relayer fee-bump means your own wallet never appears on the withdrawal."],[1091,"A relayer was unreachable at the transport level (DNS/refused/aborted/invalid body)"],[641,"A reserved enum slot for a possible future integration with a separate, external private-payments effort. It is **not implemented** and not on Shade's roadmap: every call throws `MethodNotAvailableError`."],[1153,"A stealth address is unlinkable to a meta-address without the view key. An observer sees `sender → contract` (pool) or `sender → one-time account` (account), plus `R` and `stealth_pk`, none of which reveal *you*."],[1163,"A strictly-increasing per-key nonce in contract storage."],[884,"A token bucket: **10 requests/minute per client**, `429` with `Retry-After` when empty."],[1004,"A web app should **never** hold a raw secret. Pass a signer function instead:"],[832,"Absolute outer fee cap"],[933,"Absolute outer fee cap"],[821,"Abuse guards apply on **every** path, credit-gated or not:"],[396,"Account-method Horizon paging cursor"],[1057,"Account-method XLM send ≤ 1 XLM"],[1191,"Address reuse, a linked fee-payer, or a known destination will deanonymize you regardless of the cryptography."],[131,"After the covered span, the scan **re-checks `/health` once more**: a gap the indexer recorded *while the scan was consuming its feed* discards the segment's results, and the tail re-walks the whole span, so a mid-scan hole can never advance the client cursor past a payment."],[1003,"Against a credit-gated relayer (the default), `fundingAccount` alone is not enough: the relayer requires a fresh challenge **signed** by that account, so pass `fundingSigner` too (any `(message) => signature` function: a raw keypair, a wallet, an HSM). Both fields also apply to `withdraw()`'s `WithdrawOpts`."],[249,"Alias for `--plaintext`"],[859,"All arithmetic on **BigInt stroops** — never floats."],[144,"All configuration is environment variables. `packages/indexer/.env.example` is the annotated list:"],[88,"All entries are **persistent** storage. TTLs are extended on write and, notably, **on read**: `get_balance` and `get_nonce` bump a live entry's TTL back up to the ceiling. That means a passively-scanning recipient keeps their own balance alive without ever writing."],[1047,"All exported from `stellar-shade&#x60; so apps can branch cleanly. Every error extends a shared &#x2A;*`ShadeError`*&#x2A; base and carries a stable &#x2A;*`code`** string (e.g. `method_required`, `transaction_timeout`); branch on `e.code` when `instanceof` is unreliable across bundling/realm boundaries:"],[1113,"All six exported types work in **raw bytes** (`Uint8Array`), not hex strings:"],[939,"Allowed origin"],[183,"Allowed origin, permissive **on purpose** here, unlike the relayer: the candidate feed is public data anyone can read off Horizon"],[674,"Almost always the raw-scalar footgun: you built a keypair from `recoverStealthPrivateKey`'s output via `Keypair.fromRawEd25519Seed()` (or similar), which hashes it into a *different* key. &#x2A;*Sign with `signWithStealthKey`.** See Core Concepts."],[1032,"Also exported: `challengeMessage(endpoint, fundingAccount, nonce, amount, bind?)`, the canonical proof-of-control message, which must match the relayer byte-for-byte. See Relayer."],[1038,"Also exported: `normalizeRelayList(relay?)`, the canonical `string | string[]` → clean-list normalization (`[]`/whitespace → `undefined`)."],[478,"Amount deposited, in the token's smallest unit"],[276,"Amount in whole units (e.g. `100` for 100 XLM)"],[1061,"Amount isn't a positive finite number"],[376,"Amount to withdraw (default: full balance)"],[466,"An **announcement** is the on-chain record that lets you discover a payment. In the `pool` method it's a contract storage entry created **atomically with the deposit**: no deposit, no announcement, which makes announcement spam impossible. It carries:"],[649,"An account-method XLM send must be **strictly greater than 1 XLM**. Below that the new account can't meet its base reserve. Send more, or use `method: 'pool'`, which has no such floor."],[846,"An app sends the relayer a normal XLM payment."],[1173,"An indexer can *hide* payments (an availability failure) but cannot *fabricate* them: the client derives the stealth address from `R` itself and re-verifies on-chain at claim. It serves no address- or R-keyed queries, so the operator cannot link keys to requests; every scan ends with a Horizon tail and falls back to Horizon on any fault."],[1095,"An indexer endpoint responded non-2xx; carries `.status` and the indexer's own `.indexerCode`. The scan treats it as \"fall back to the Horizon walk\""],[130,"An indexer fault **mid-scan** degrades automatically to the Horizon walk from the last good cursor."],[1097,"An indexer was unreachable at the transport level (DNS/refused/timeout/invalid body); same Horizon fallback"],[414,"Announcement"],[307,"Announcement indexer URL for fast account-method discovery. Falls back to `$SHADE_INDEXER`; Horizon remains the source of truth"],[321,"Announcement indexer URL for fast account-method discovery. Falls back to `$SHADE_INDEXER`; Horizon remains the source of truth"],[518,"Any SAC token (XLM, USDC, …)"],[348,"App account to debit a credit-gated relayer fee against"],[384,"App account to debit a credit-gated relayer fee against"],[257,"Application id to scope derived keys (default: `default`)"],[798,"Apps and users can hand the SDK/CLI **several** relayer URLs instead of one (`ClientConfig.relayer: string[]`, CLI `--relay a,b` or the `SHADE_RELAYERS` env var). The client then health-probes every candidate in parallel and routes each relayed submission to a healthy one, failing over on relayer faults. See SDK Reference → RelayerPool for the exact health rule and failover semantics. A candidate counts as healthy only when its `/health` reports `status: 'ok'` on the right network with a workable balance, **and** its credit gate is passable by this caller. This is where the `store`/`sharedState` fields also let a client prefer a durable (`postgres`/`redis`) deployment over a dev-fallback one."],[1,"Architecture"],[1222,"Architecture — where each control is implemented"],[482,"Architecture: how these concepts map onto components"],[771,"Architecture: the components and how data flows between them"],[585,"Architecture: the data flow behind each method"],[271,"Argument"],[325,"Argument"],[361,"Argument"],[354,"Asset to claim, pool method: `native` or `CODE:ISSUER`"],[286,"Asset to send (default: native XLM, or `CODE:ISSUER`)"],[378,"Asset to withdraw (default: native XLM, or `CODE:ISSUER`)"],[53,"Atomic deposit + announcement. `sender.require_auth()`."],[7,"Authorization model"],[869,"Backs"],[322,"Balances are aggregated per token in stroops and displayed with a readable asset label (`XLM` rather than the native SAC `C...` address)."],[558,"Base account reserve"],[546,"Because there is no view tag, **every hash-memo transaction on the network is a discovery candidate**. An unassisted scan walks the global Horizon transaction feed client-side, which makes a cold scan for a fresh recipient take minutes (and grow with the network). The fix is the **announcement indexer** (`packages/indexer`): a standalone service that walks the feed server-side **once for everyone**, keeps only hash-memo candidates with their operations, and serves them as a compact feed the client filters **locally**. It deliberately answers no address- or R-keyed queries, so the operator cannot link keys to requests. Point the SDK at one with `ClientConfig.indexe