finity`."],[234,"every command (keystore path)"],[1046,"Every failure is typed so the scan can treat it as \"fall back to the Horizon walk\", never as a lost payment: transport failures and timeouts throw &#x2A;*`IndexerNetworkError`** (code `indexer_network_error&#x60;); non-2xx responses throw &#x2A;*`IndexerHttpError`** (code `indexer_http_error`), carrying the HTTP `.status` and the indexer's own `.indexerCode` from its `{ error, code }` body. Also exported: the `IndexerHealth`, `IndexerAnnouncement`, and `AnnouncementsPage` types."],[136,"Every failure mode degrades `/health` (`status: 'degraded'`, each cause exposed individually): a recorded **gap**, a **suspected testnet reset** (cursor impossibly far past the chain head, confirmed twice and then *latched* until restart, so a stale-era database never becomes trustworthy again just because the new chain outgrows it), a **persistently failing continuity check** (`continuityStale`: gap/reset detection is effectively off, so coverage cannot be vouched for), and a **stalled ingest loop** (`stalled`: a frozen indexer must not report `ok` forever). SDK guards require `status: 'ok'`, so every degraded state routes clients back to Horizon automatically. A hole can never *hide* a payment, it only costs speed."],[129,"Every scan **finishes with a Horizon tail** from the final cursor, so indexer lag cannot hide a payment."],[208,"Every shade CLI command and flag: keygen, address, send, scan, balance, claim and withdraw, plus secret handling and the encrypted keystore format."],[990,"Every symbol on this page is exported from the package named in its heading."],[1101,"Exact stroop conversion (no float drift)"],[673,"Expected in one case: `balance` suppresses fully-swept native accounts (live balance 0). For pool announcements the two commands can't diverge, because `balance` reuses `scan`'s paged fetch and pages the full set."],[39,"Express service: fee-bump, sponsored claims, credit ledger."],[42,"Express service: ingest